content.detailedDescription:
Driving back home to st. louis from the hot springs ar area, it was about 9:45 pm and we were in cape girardeau mo. i'd been driving for 5 3/4 hours, and still had another 1 3/4 to get home, so i was mainly concentrating on the road. when about a mile from the southeast medical plaza, which i could see, i noticed what at first appeared to be a large sized commercial airliner approaching a runway, taking its near landing approach across i-55 and over the plaza. i couldn't help but notice this as it was taking place directly in my line of vision. i live in st. louis about six miles from its international airport and am quite familiar with approaching aircraft to an airport. these lights were at a declining angle towards the ground, passing over the plaza at about 500', the length of lights about 300' in length. having better than common familiarity with conventional aircraft lighting, i couldn't quite discern what i was seeing, also wondering why in the large expanse of land available would a runway by built just a few hundred yards east of the plaza? i didn't think cape girardeau had a commercial airport, so i asked my passenger and she said she didn't think so either, and then mentioned that she'd seen some other strange lights just before acknowledging the lights passing in front of us when i asked her if she knew what they were (no). as we passed the plaza, i quickly glanced a few times expecting to see the the craft coming down to a runway, but as i last saw it it instead seemed to have banked right slightly and had leveled off! i was confused, i'd just seen at least six distinct lights that appeared to be fixed to a single indiscernible "airplane" decline down to the ground right in front of me but level off and bank right, a craft least had to be 300' long from first light to last light. the front light was white, steady but strobbing. then there was a distance and there were two white lights close together - these three white lights seeming to be "in-line" on the craft. the last three lights were in a tight triangle a distance from the two "middle" lights, but appearing to be slightly higher "in-line" on the craft. if the object were a plane, the front light appeared to be under the nose, the two lights under the center where the wings would be, and the last three as a small triangle in the middle of the tail of the "airplane". the top lights was green and the two bottom lights were red. this did not appear to be an faa regulation lighting arrangement for a helicopter nor airplane based on the direction of travel of the craft. when i noticed the strange green and reds triangle, i remember having read that when seeing strange lights that one should try to discern a pattern to the lights. i would say the pattern i've described i saw more than once when looking and glancing at the lights, but the rear triangle of green and reds sometimes appeared to be white instead, where sometimes they were green and reds, and sometimes they were white. anyways, i and a passenger witness thought these lights were strange, seeming to be on approach to an airport that wasn't quite there.

since that sighting, i did some research using internet maps and found that i had just passed the cape girardeau regional airport about a mile before i started seeing the lights passing over i-55 and the southeast medical plaza! it was because of the street view of the maps that i figured out it was passing over the southeast medical plaza, at the time i only knew i was in cape girardeau and hadn't realized i'd just passed the regional airport!! note again, just passed the regional airport, it was behind me at the time i saw the lights. so, ironically, i'd just passed an airport without realizing it and was passing a sign with the mileage to st. louis (where i was going) without realizing it when i was actually seeing the craft!!! anyways, hopefully there is an image associated with this report depicting what i and my passenger witnessed in cape girardeau as we were approaching and passing the southeast medical plaza at about 9:43 pm as memorial day evening.
content.summary: Strange lights (craft?) descend over cape girardeau

content.detailedDescription: We were at the edge of the boardwalk in seaside heights nj..As far out into the ocean at edge of pier as possible. it was pretty strange.It was just a large cloud cover rolled in off the ocean, coming towards us.As it got closer it was just different.As the large cloud got close to the pier it turned to our rite and continued heading south along the beach.But out over the water..As it went away from us,and it was still very close at the time. we could easily make out 6 to 8 turbine type emissions from the rear,,although there was no sound. at least not that we could hear, and again, we were very close.But also all the rides and boardwalk noise was loud,along with the waves of the ocean. this vehicle was the most amazing thing i have ever scene.Because of the heavy cloud cover surrounding most of it,the rear with its flame type emission was the only very clear section,,it hovered a good 10 to 15 feet off the water..Keeping in mind also. there were no other clouds in the sky.It was a clear night. also when i say it had 6 to 8 turbine like emissions in the rear..The closest thing to compare these emissions to would be like the end of a propane torch,,only each exhaust was much larger..This was a pretty large vehicle..It hovered effortlessly,without displacing any water below..It continued slowly down shoreline hovering over water,,a good 75 to 100 yards from where water meets the sand again heading south. as it moved away the fire like exhaust was eventually covered by cloud . we watched it in amazement till it was out of sight.We looked at each other and we each asked the other if they saw that.We both agreed we did  and never spoke of it again ever since..I was in awe after seeing it..I know we seen something very strange that night..I had never seen anything like it before or since..For you people into this stuff,,you would of loved it..I'm not into this stuff and i was grateful and amazed at seeing it..Not sure how i would of felt if there wasn't someone else there that saw exactly what i did..
content.summary: On a clear nite a vehicle with flame type exhaust appeared out of nowhere.

content.detailedDescription:
I was investigating events from the previous night as reported by a group of blue springs missouri residents and since i witnessed this the previous night with the group wanted to look at this from a different vantage point.  i went to a park in eastern jackson county where there is less light pollution. at 8:45 pm i went to the little blue park on 78 highway east of the independence power plant which is a wooded area and clearing and has no lighting so there is less light pollution here. this is only about a mile away from the neighborhood on 30th terr. s where we were last night.  my husband, two daughters, and two grandsons came along.  we first observed one object appear at dusk in the ene at 30 degrees from the horizon.  the object was flashing red, green, and white colors very distinctly which were visible to the naked eye, and the object appeared large.  a sheriff came by and asked what we were doing and he said that he noticed the object as well and thought that it was odd.  we observed the same characteristics, only clearer, through high-powered binoculars.  i took some long exposure photos with a nikon camera but nothing showed up on the photos. we also noticed several bright white streaks in the sky during the 3 hours we were at this location. 

at 10:30 pm my daughter arrived with a large 12��� telescope and we observed the object with the computer attached to the telescope.  by that time the object has faded away and was gone.  

1. the object looked large and very bright
2. there were distinct, red, white, and blue colors pulsing in sequence that we timed at 2-second intervals using high-powered binoculars.
3. i saw features including a large black circle, which moved to the left and it appeared that the entire object moved 90 degrees counter-clockwise. 
4. i saw a bright white line move up and down in front of it and a grid pattern over it. 
5. my daughter saw a yellow outer ring and purple colors pulsing inside (possibly due to the red and blue colors mixing). she also saw a bright white line and the black circle moving along with a grid pattern.
content.summary: Large bright object with red, white, and blue lights

content.detailedDescription:
As reported to asd by phone today: 

i have been observing some very strange lights over independence for the past five days when i get home from work. i live in east independence and from my place of work in kansas city this is not visible. it looks like the same object returns each night in the east ne sky.  it looks like a craft that glows white with red and blue lights on it that pulse, or a white, red, and blue light that pulses.  i have looked at this through binoculars and can clearly see these pulsing lights in the sky that have never been there before.  i have lived here for 35 years and have never seen anything like it.  i spent two hours looking at it on one evening and it remained in the exact same spot and did not move like the stars do over time.  i called my friend in grandview and he is seeing the same thing from his position.  on another night it looked like the object was moving around in a circle.  we are perplexed by these bright neon-like lights and also the size of it - the thing looks very big - it would take a penny to cover it up at arms length.
content.summary: Stationary object with flashing lights over independence for five nights

content.detailedDescription:
As reported to asd in person on may 28: 

six of us were leaving a restaurant and traveling in two cars.  we headed to drop off some of our party.  we were driving west on highway 7 and as we approached the stoplight at 2nd street all of us (four of us in my car and two in another car in front of us) all saw a craft of some type in the sky just below the clouds.  it had four rectangular windows in it.  the car in front of us saw it first and got a better view of the object.  the two people in the car in front of us said that they saw thin humanoid type beings standing in two of the windows, which emmitted a yellowish glow from inside the craft. no one in my car saw the beings but we did clearly see the windows and saw the craft back up, move down a bit, then move up into the coulds.  there were no lights on the outside of the craft and it was so dark that it was difficult to see the shape of it so all we could clearly see were the four horizontal windows with a light inside of them.  our friends in the first vehicle are so shaken by this that they refuse to talk about it any more.  i am reporting this because i think you should know about the incident. surely other people saw it as well.  i just can't believe it - we are all very practical people and no one has seen a ufo before, but i believe that was exactly what we saw.  since that night i've been seeing some strange big white and amber lights in the sky that look like they have webs over them and pulse different colors.  i've never seen these before, either. i would like to know what is going on.
content.summary: Large craft with windows and humanoids witnessed by six people

content.detailedDescription: I was on my porch smoking. there was a blue flash in the sky as the streetlights went out. another flash killed all the house lights except a select few houses still had power. by this time i was looking to the sky adn there was one more flash of blue as every hair on my body stood up like a static bomb been dropped and there was a streak through the sky from the point it took off there was a wider trail than in the direction it was going > like that it was a trail of emisson coming off from the light trail. at this time all the power came back on. then there was a plane that flew the same direction after the light. i knew the sound of the plane but the lights had no sounds jus flashes and a streak. this was at 2:22 am on may 30 2012 montgomery, wv.
content.summary: Blue flas of light streetlights went out followed by another flash houses lost power then another flash and streak across sky and everyhair on my body stood up from static as power came back on.

content.detailedDescription:
As reported to asd by phone on may 29: 

for the past two weeks my family and i have been observing some strange objects in the sky that we have never seen before.  we live in an area with few neighbors and have a good view of the night sky.  my teenage son first saw these and pointed them out to us.  he is an ameteur astronomer and has his telescope out several nights a week. i am an instructor at a local college and my husband is a physician.  we thought they were planets at first, but these were not in the correct places and were too large.  one of the objects is approximately three times the size of saturn.  the objects are bright white in color and pulse different colors in timed sequence every second or every two seconds, and the colors are very bright. 

we watched three of these objects, one in the west and two in the northest sky at approximately 40 degrees from the horizon.  through the telescope it appears as if a white glowing grid is over the front of each of these, making them appear to have structure. at approximately 11:15 pm on may 23 after we had watched these for a couple of hours one of these objects dropped down to tree top level and stayed in that position for approximately ten minutes, then shot straight up in the air at light speed and out of sight. at that point, all five of us packed up our equipment and ran back into the house.  we realized that what we had been looking at was probably not man-made, or if it was it was highly unusual.  

we saw planes and jets in the area, and have seen planes nightly, some going near the objects and some appearing to circle them.  we can't tell distance, but they do look like they are fairly close to us.  i saw the reports on tv and decided to let someone know what we saw so you can investigate it, but i don't want any publicity and don't want to talk to any media.  i attempted to get photographs but nothing appears on the photos - the distance may be too great.
content.summary: Three objects appear nightly for the past two weeks

content.detailedDescription:
1. my husband and i were outside enjoying watching the night sky.
2. the object simply appeared directly overhead and fell straight downward for some distance and then abruptly stopped.  did not remain hovering, but made a direction change of 90 degrees and headed north, parallel to the earth until we could no longer see it.
3. we did not think it resembled anything we'd ever seen, it behaved as though it was controlled.  we couldn't determine what it could be.
4. the object was a star-like (bright white light), round, suddenly appeared from straight up above us, dropped downward for a time, stopped, made a 90 degree direction change and moved north (at moderate speed) away from us, staying constantly lit the entire time it was visible to us.
5. it was cool to see, even though it wasn't especially "spectacular" in shape or color.
6. it simply was too far for us to see any longer.
content.summary: Bright white light appeared, fell straight downward, stopped and turned 90 degrees, parallel to the ground and moved in a straight line toward the horizon.

content.detailedDescription: My son and his friend and i were taking video of lightning when we saw the star like light fly and flutter in light faster than anything i ever seen before....Im an aviation maintenance student and study flight characteristics every day...I can't explain what it is ..We have video evidence of the event i have the video and so does my sons friend i just can't figure out how to attach it
content.summary: A star like disoriented path taken right after a few lightning strikes a star like feature jetting around the sky i have video

content.detailedDescription: Driving in car in bellevue, near freeway, and noticed 2 bright lights in the sky, at first glance we thought they were helicopters or planes, but with a closer look we noticed they were diamond, or square shaped with 3 lights, 2 blinking (1 red, 1 blue) and one bright one that formed a sort of prong shape. after a while, we had seen at least 8, and noticed they were changing direction, they were all rather close together. then, once we were off the freeway, at an empty intersection we saw a ninth one, flying very, very fast and very low, the lowest we had seen, just above the roofs of buildings. then as we were watching it abruptly came to a complete stop, hovered for a while, which was really freaky, because we were the only ones at the intersection, it was almost as if it saw us watching it.  then immediately got back up to speed, and bolted out of sight. we didn't see anymore after that. we were so intrigued, that we called some friends and family to ask what they knew about this.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: 9 diamond shaped aircrafts flying close together.

content.detailedDescription: Holy crap where do i begin???? i went back outside to see if i could see the blinking starlike objects and instead of one or two i found three this time. two were about 45 degrees elevation the other one was about 30 degrees elevation in the west/ northwest. as i was looking at those i saw out of the corner of my eye something flash very brightly, when i looked straight up a saw what looked like debri falling into the atmosphere going from south to west. it had a long firey tail and i watched it fall closer to the earth when it stopped suddenly at about 100-200 feet above land and turned north. as it went further away the light faded out and i lost sight. i swear im not making this up. it was the weirdest thing ive seen yet. i tried to get my camera phone to take a picture but it wouldnt unlock until the flying object had disappeared. weirdest thing ever.... what is up with all this stuff happening out here?? anyone figure it out yet or have theories????? i tried to get video and pictures of the blinking lights but im not sure that my camera could pick it up.
content.summary: Blinking starlike objects with firey flying object with directional change

content.detailedDescription:
I was driving along division street in stevens point, wi, at approximately 7:38pm, tuesday, may 29th, when i saw a metallic silver spherical object hovering in the sky in front of me at about 30' off the horizon.  i immediately recognized that it was not an airplane or helicopter as it was completely round, hovered, and had no blinking lights.  

i kept my eyes on the object as i went through an intersection and observed it for appoximately 15 seconds before it simply disappeared.  i pulled the car over and parked along division street.  i scanned the sky for the object and it appeared again approximately 30 seconds later. it was in basically the same place, though a few degrees off from its original position.  once again, it appeared to be a metalic silver spherical object with a very distinct outline - no lights, wings, rotors.  i watched it for approximately 10 seconds before it disappeared or "winked out" once again.  

i continued to sit in the same position and scan the sky for 10 more minutes, but did not see it again.  

note 1: i don't know if it's relevant or not, but observing the object did not make me feel excited, scared or uneasy; i simply felt as if i was observing any other sort of unusual object.  

note 2: this is the second time i have seen an object in the air above stevens point, wi, that fits the description of the object listed above. i did not report the object the first time i saw it.
content.summary: I observed a solid spherical object hover in the air, disappear, reappear and then disappear.

i kept my eyes on the object as i went through an intersection and observed it for appoximately 15 seconds before it simply disappeared.  i pulled the car over and parked along division street.  i scanned the sky for the object and it appeared again approximately 30 seconds later. it was in basically the same place, though a few degrees off from its original position.  once again, it appeared to be a metalic silver spherical object with a very distinct outline - no lights, wings, rotors.  i watched it for approximately 10 seconds before it disappeared or "winked out" once again.  

i continued to sit in the same position and scan the sky for 10 more minutes, but did not see it again.  

note 1: i don't know if it's relevant or not, but observing the object did not make me feel excited, scared or uneasy; i simply felt as if i was observing any other sort of object.  

note 2: this is the second time i have seen an object in the air above stevens point, wi, that fits the description of the object listed above. i did not report the object the first time i saw it.
content.summary: I observed a solid spherical object hover in the air, disappear, reappear and then disappear.
